name: Governor Dan McKee

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: In the past year we have achieved an unprecedented rebound. We reopened our economy, kept our kids in school, and put families back to work! tweet: We have work to do – and we’re going to get it done. Because we will have a bright future in the next four years by working together.

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: In the year ahead, we’ll be cutting taxes for veterans, growing the jobs of the future, and investing in a once-in-a-generation effort to add affordable housing.

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: I’m running to create good jobs for those who need them, grow our economy in every corner of our state, and raise per capita income for everyone.

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: I will continue to support our small businesses to keep the economic engine of our state humming. Rhode Island has given $18M to help small businesses and more help is on the way.

name: Governor Dan McKee
tweet: My message to Rhode Island today is simple: I’m running for re-election to lower costs for working people--to make it easier for you to get by and to put money back in your pockets, where it belongs.

tweet: Big news: I’m running for re-election! We’ve worked hard to get vaccines out in our communities, support our businesses, and improve education. Thanks to your support, Rhode Island has momentum.  https://t.co/zIvzBdsiL7
